WEBVTT

00:03.571 --> 00:04.703
Adult mark:<i> In</i>
<i> the summer of</i> 1987,

00:04.838 --> 00:07.439
<i> I became a working man.</i>

00:07.508 --> 00:10.308
<i> My brother had always</i>
<i> mowed the lawn at vocm.</i>

00:10.378 --> 00:12.710
<i> But now that he was leaving</i>
<i> the nest for university,</i>

00:12.747 --> 00:15.580
<i> It fell to me to keep</i>
<i>the grass at an even two inches.</i>

00:15.616 --> 00:19.117
<i> The only problem was,</i>
<i> I was deathly allergic.</i>

00:19.153 --> 00:21.653
<i> And very, very weak.</i>

00:21.722 --> 00:23.822
[lawnmower starts]

00:25.159 --> 00:26.925
["walkin' on sunshine"
by katrina and the waves plays]

00:26.927 --> 00:28.860
Adult mark:<i> For</i>
the first time in my life,

00:28.896 --> 00:30.328
<i> I wanted summer to end.</i>

00:30.364 --> 00:33.331
<i> I had played my cards</i>
<i> close to my wheezing chest.</i>

00:33.333 --> 00:36.001
<i> Summer had separated me</i>
<i> from my school crush,</i>

00:36.003 --> 00:38.169
<i> And the drama made me</i>
<i> feel like I was living</i>

00:38.205 --> 00:41.406
<i> In one of the old movies</i>
<i> that I loved.</i>

00:41.409 --> 00:43.609
Fox: I'm coming with you
to your weird house.

00:43.611 --> 00:44.676
Mark: No.

00:44.678 --> 00:46.745
You're getting on that bus,
where you belong.

00:46.747 --> 00:49.081
You'll be alone
all summer, nerd!

00:49.083 --> 00:50.882
You're saying this
only to make me go.

00:52.086 --> 00:54.286
I'm saying it
because it's true.

00:54.288 --> 00:55.788
If that bus leaves to school
and you're not on it,

00:55.923 --> 00:57.022
You'll regret it.
Fox: No.

00:57.091 --> 00:59.825
Mark: Maybe not today,
maybe not tomorrow, but soon,

00:59.894 --> 01:01.093
And for the rest of your life.

01:01.162 --> 01:04.096
[bus starts]

01:04.165 --> 01:05.497
Fox: But what about us?

01:06.567 --> 01:08.166
We'll always have recess.

01:09.236 --> 01:10.835
I guess.

01:10.871 --> 01:13.906
See on the bus, dumbass.

01:14.041 --> 01:15.440
Mark: No...

01:15.509 --> 01:16.574
No...

01:16.610 --> 01:17.709
No!

01:17.778 --> 01:18.777
Nooo!

01:18.912 --> 01:20.646
Dick: No, boy!

01:20.781 --> 01:22.714
Nooo!

01:22.750 --> 01:24.850
♪

01:24.985 --> 01:27.519
Mark: Oh, no.

01:27.654 --> 01:30.322
Oh, no!

01:30.324 --> 01:34.259
[kettle whistling]

01:34.328 --> 01:36.060
Mark: Pop!
Gross!

01:36.097 --> 01:37.563
Pop: A sink is a sink.

01:37.565 --> 01:39.531
Your father is still
on the toilet!

01:39.567 --> 01:41.300
Mark: So?
Wait your turn!

01:41.302 --> 01:42.501
Pop: Are you mad?

01:42.636 --> 01:44.436
Do you know
how many people I know

01:44.438 --> 01:45.803
Who have lost their teeth?

01:45.840 --> 01:48.673
Gumming their food
with smiles like ducks.

01:48.709 --> 01:50.842
You know, I'm the
only one from my class

01:50.911 --> 01:54.346
That can actually eat
an apple without glue.

01:54.415 --> 01:57.015
I've got teeth like a zipper!

01:57.051 --> 01:58.350
Mary: Here.

01:58.352 --> 02:00.886
Put your teeth to use.

02:00.888 --> 02:02.020
You're up early.

02:02.056 --> 02:04.623
Nobody in this house has
ever wanted to go to school.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.192
And you smell... Nice.

02:07.194 --> 02:08.593
[sighs]
yeah, um...

02:08.629 --> 02:11.029
Two squirts of
mike's drakar noir.

02:11.065 --> 02:12.430
Mary: Oh!
Mark: Too much?

02:12.432 --> 02:13.698
Just enough.

02:13.700 --> 02:15.434
Pop: Smells like puberty to me.

02:15.569 --> 02:17.302
Mark: Pop!
Pop: Well, it's true.

02:17.437 --> 02:18.937
I mean, you're
becoming a man now!

02:18.939 --> 02:22.374
Sudden interest in girls,
hair popping up everywhere,

02:22.509 --> 02:24.443
A set of permanent teeth...

02:24.578 --> 02:26.011
Mary: Well, he still
has one baby tooth,

02:26.146 --> 02:27.579
So he's still my baby!

02:27.714 --> 02:28.847
[kisses]

02:28.849 --> 02:29.981
Mike sr: Mary?

02:30.017 --> 02:31.382
Can you help me with my tie?

02:31.418 --> 02:32.651
<i> One of</i> my babies.

02:32.786 --> 02:34.820
Adult mark:<i> While I had</i>
<i> shamed my old man at work...</i>

02:34.955 --> 02:36.021
Mike jr: I'm home!

02:36.156 --> 02:37.723
Adult mark: ...<i> My brother</i>
<i> filled him with pride.</i>

02:37.858 --> 02:39.424
<i> By working</i>
<i> at the radio station</i>

02:39.426 --> 02:40.993
<i> To help pay for university,</i>

02:40.995 --> 02:43.762
<i> He was rebelling</i>
<i> by slowly becoming my father.</i>

02:43.831 --> 02:45.664
Hi.
Bye.

02:45.733 --> 02:47.198
Mike sr: How was
your day at work?

02:47.334 --> 02:48.667
Oh, you mean "night"?

02:48.669 --> 02:50.468
Yeah, I'm friggin' wiped, but...

02:50.504 --> 02:52.004
Finally getting
the hang of the board.

02:52.139 --> 02:55.139
So, you think maybe I could come
in for a day shift sometime?

02:55.176 --> 02:57.142
Even hop on air?
'cause I think I could--

02:57.277 --> 02:59.678
You've got bigger fish
to fry than radio.

02:59.747 --> 03:02.380
The first critch
to go to university.

03:02.416 --> 03:04.082
Mary: Oh, that university
still hasn't cashed

03:04.151 --> 03:05.417
That tuition cheque!

03:05.552 --> 03:08.019
I wish they'd hurry up and get
the money out of the account.

03:08.055 --> 03:09.154
I'm terrified to buy anything!

03:09.223 --> 03:12.157
Mike jr: Ah, I wouldn't
worry too much about that.

03:12.226 --> 03:13.358
Alright, I'm heading to bed.

03:13.493 --> 03:15.427
Pop: Make sure you
brush your teeth first!

03:15.496 --> 03:17.162
You remember
len marshall, right?

03:17.297 --> 03:18.964
It turns out
he's got false teeth.

03:18.966 --> 03:21.900
I mean, I never knew this,
but it came out in conversation.

03:22.035 --> 03:24.436
No, and literally came out,
the dentures...

03:24.438 --> 03:27.372
Flew out onto the table!

03:27.507 --> 03:29.608
Turns out they belong
to his dead wife.

03:29.743 --> 03:32.511
But he's such a cheapskate
that he wouldn't get a new set.

03:32.513 --> 03:34.979
Her jaw was bigger than his.

03:35.015 --> 03:36.515
She had a head like a melon.

03:36.650 --> 03:38.149
Mike jr: Night, pop.
Pop: Morning.

03:38.185 --> 03:39.718
Mark: Right, I'm off.

03:39.720 --> 03:41.119
Don't want to miss my bus!

03:41.155 --> 03:42.254
See ya!

03:42.389 --> 03:44.522
Ah, gawd.

03:45.459 --> 03:46.758
Puberty.

03:46.794 --> 03:50.195
[upbeat music]

03:50.197 --> 03:54.066
[indistinct chatter]

03:54.201 --> 03:56.868
[music slows]

03:59.240 --> 04:04.209
Adult mark:<i> No fox.</i>

04:04.278 --> 04:05.944
<i> But her brothers were there.</i>

04:06.079 --> 04:08.046
New year, same dork.

04:09.083 --> 04:10.148
Where's fox?

04:10.217 --> 04:11.917
Silver fox: Aww, you hear that?

04:12.052 --> 04:15.219
Little nerd wants to know
where our sister is.

04:15.256 --> 04:17.488
Middle fox: Our sister's
too hot for you!

04:17.490 --> 04:18.956
Mark: You think
your own sister's hot?

04:18.993 --> 04:21.226
Silver fox: Yeah...
What the hell, man?

04:21.295 --> 04:22.894
Middle fox: What?
No, gross!

04:22.930 --> 04:24.362
Silver fox: Wait...

04:24.498 --> 04:25.563
You don't know!

04:25.633 --> 04:27.265
Adult mark:<i> For the first time</i>
<i> in their lives,</i>

04:27.400 --> 04:29.468
<i>The fox brothers knew something</i>
<i> that someone else didn't.</i>

04:29.603 --> 04:30.635
Mark: What?

04:30.704 --> 04:32.637
What is it?
Where is she?

04:32.640 --> 04:34.772
Middle fox: He don't even know
she got a boyfriend,

04:34.808 --> 04:37.175
And we're not gonna tell him!

04:37.310 --> 04:39.411
What?

04:39.546 --> 04:40.712
Adult mark:<i> A boyfriend?</i>

04:40.781 --> 04:43.648
<i> I'd been listening</i>
<i> to a mixtape of lies.</i>

04:43.684 --> 04:45.850
<i> Unless they were</i>
<i> the ones lying to me.</i>

04:45.886 --> 04:48.119
Silver fox: I wants the window!
Middle fox: I wants it!

04:48.155 --> 04:49.287
[loud smack]
middle fox: Ah!

04:49.290 --> 04:50.822
Adult mark:<i> But chances were,</i>
<i> the fox brothers</i>

04:50.957 --> 04:52.256
<i> Weren't smart enough for that.</i>

04:52.293 --> 04:54.926
Middle fox: Awww, b'y!
My head!

04:54.995 --> 04:57.128
♪

05:01.535 --> 05:03.201
Ritchie: Mark!
Hey!

05:03.203 --> 05:06.237
Grade eight!
I'm stoked!

05:06.273 --> 05:07.272
Mark: Hey.

05:07.407 --> 05:09.541
Ritchie: These are
my new friends.

05:09.610 --> 05:12.077
They live by me!
Isn't that crazy?

05:12.146 --> 05:13.411
Adult mark:<i> New friends?</i>

05:13.447 --> 05:15.147
<i>Had everyone forgotten about me?</i>

05:15.282 --> 05:16.415
Ritchie: Check it out.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.883
I can skateboard now!

05:22.222 --> 05:23.355
Wanna try?

05:23.490 --> 05:24.523
No, thank you.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.425
I don't skate...

05:26.427 --> 05:28.093
Or ride a bike.

05:28.162 --> 05:30.161
I'm not into transit.

05:30.197 --> 05:32.263
[tires squealing]

05:32.333 --> 05:38.302
["rock you like a hurricane"
by the scorpions plays]

05:38.339 --> 05:40.939
<i> ♪ here I am ♪</i>

05:41.008 --> 05:42.640
<i> ♪ rock you like a hurricane ♪</i>

05:42.676 --> 05:45.277
Ritchie: That kid
looks too young to drive.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.045
Adult mark:<i> Millard mcginty!</i>

05:47.114 --> 05:49.915
<i> A tenth-grader brazen enough</i>
<i> to drive on a learner's permit</i>

05:49.917 --> 05:52.417
<i> Without an adult</i>
<i> present in the car!</i>

05:52.552 --> 05:54.319
Ritchie: Wait...

05:54.321 --> 05:55.920
♪

05:55.989 --> 05:59.190
<i> ♪ lust is in cages</i>
<i> 'til storm breaks loose</i> ♪

05:59.226 --> 06:03.662
<i> ♪ just have to make it</i>
<i> with someone I choose ♪</i>

06:03.797 --> 06:06.498
Ritchie: Are they dating?
Mark: Shut up.

06:06.633 --> 06:07.866
Ritchie: I didn't do anything!

06:08.001 --> 06:10.602
<i> ♪ the wolf is hungry,</i>
<i> he runs the show... ♪</i>

06:10.604 --> 06:14.139
Silver fox: Ha!
Told ya.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.206
[engine revs]

06:22.483 --> 06:27.752
[emotional music]

06:27.821 --> 06:31.356
♪

06:31.491 --> 06:36.027
[school bell rings]

06:42.035 --> 06:45.303
Yes, michael f. Critch junior
is the name.

06:45.372 --> 06:47.305
Well, no, that can't be right.

06:47.441 --> 06:51.176
Well, 'cause I
registered him myself.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.245
Cancelled?

06:53.247 --> 06:56.714
Are you sure?

06:56.750 --> 07:01.519
Well, thank you so much.
You've been very helpful.

07:01.555 --> 07:04.789
That sneaky little shagger.

07:04.825 --> 07:07.658
♪

07:07.694 --> 07:11.796
[indistinct chatter]

07:11.832 --> 07:13.064
Ow!

07:13.066 --> 07:15.333
Middle fox: Stop staring
at my sister's desk, perv.

07:15.402 --> 07:17.602
Adult mark:<i> While his</i>
<i> sister had outgrown me,</i>

07:17.638 --> 07:19.003
<i> Her brother had devolved,</i>

07:19.039 --> 07:21.740
<i> Repeating the grade</i>
<i> for the second time.</i>

07:21.875 --> 07:24.075
Just pick on
someone your own size.

07:24.144 --> 07:25.010
Oh, that's right.

07:25.145 --> 07:27.178
Everyone your size
is in high school.

07:27.214 --> 07:28.747
Just 'cause I failed again

07:28.749 --> 07:32.717
Don't make you
the same age as me.

07:32.853 --> 07:35.287
Attention, students.

07:35.422 --> 07:37.088
I have some...

07:37.090 --> 07:39.123
Unsettling news.

07:39.159 --> 07:41.593
I know that many of you expected
that sister margaret

07:41.728 --> 07:43.562
Would be your teacher this year.

07:43.697 --> 07:45.830
I am sorry to be
the one to tell you this,

07:45.899 --> 07:48.432
But sister margaret is dead.

07:48.469 --> 07:50.535
[students gasping]

07:50.604 --> 07:52.237
Mark: But... How?

07:52.306 --> 07:53.672
Sister rose: Metaphorically.

07:53.807 --> 07:59.177
She was "killed" by your
new teacher, ms. Fowler.

07:59.246 --> 08:00.445
Come in!

08:00.447 --> 08:02.080
Get it over with.

08:02.149 --> 08:07.085
[upbeat music]

08:07.220 --> 08:08.953
Hello, children.

08:09.089 --> 08:09.988
Sister?

08:10.123 --> 08:13.658
Sister rose: I told you!
Sister margaret is gone.

08:13.660 --> 08:16.461
And in her place we have...

08:16.596 --> 08:18.563
Ms. Fowler.

08:19.533 --> 08:21.299
Oh, yes, mark?

08:21.301 --> 08:23.267
What is happening?

08:23.303 --> 08:24.803
Well, over the summer--

08:24.938 --> 08:27.005
Sister rose: Ms. Fowler
renounced her vows.

08:27.074 --> 08:30.141
Vows of poverty,
obedience, and...

08:30.210 --> 08:31.676
Chastity.

08:31.745 --> 08:34.746
"for a spirit of harlotry
has led them astray.

08:34.881 --> 08:37.949
"and they have
played the harlot,

08:37.951 --> 08:41.753
"departing from their vows."
hosea 4:12.

08:41.755 --> 08:44.089
Fox: You<i> dumped</i> god?

08:44.091 --> 08:45.222
Wicked!

08:45.259 --> 08:47.692
Sister rose: Yes, child.
It is most certainly wicked!

08:47.827 --> 08:50.028
Fox: Wicked means good, sister.

08:50.163 --> 08:51.896
Mark: What's so "good"
about this?

08:51.899 --> 08:53.164
You can't just love god in June

08:53.200 --> 08:56.001
And love somebody else
in September!

08:56.003 --> 08:57.435
Ms. Fowler: Well,
I'm not in love--

08:57.437 --> 08:58.502
Fox: Shut up!

08:58.539 --> 09:00.105
Maybe she just got lonely.

09:00.240 --> 09:03.308
Mark: Well, maybe god
at least deserved a phone call!

09:06.346 --> 09:09.014
I... I mean, a prayer.

09:09.149 --> 09:10.715
Sister rose: See
what you have done?

09:10.717 --> 09:13.251
If it were up to me, I'd
cast you from the faculty

09:13.386 --> 09:14.452
Like lucifer from heaven!

09:14.588 --> 09:17.655
Ms. Fowler: Uh, for the record,
I still love jesus,

09:17.724 --> 09:18.990
Just not in...

09:19.125 --> 09:20.591
That way.

09:20.627 --> 09:22.326
Take out your scribblers,
children.

09:22.328 --> 09:24.396
Adult mark:<i> As fox had</i>
<i> blossomed into womanhood,</i>

09:24.398 --> 09:27.232
<i> Sister margaret had</i>
<i> gone from nun to fun.</i>

09:27.234 --> 09:32.470
<i> Even a nun hit</i>
<i> puberty before I did.</i>

09:32.606 --> 09:33.772
Mike jr: Mom!
What the hell?

09:33.774 --> 09:35.674
Mary: Rise and shine,
professor pants-on-fire.

09:35.676 --> 09:37.576
I called the school.

09:37.711 --> 09:39.878
I...
I was gonna tell you.

09:40.013 --> 09:42.346
I swear.
I-I tried, but...

09:42.382 --> 09:43.547
Dad.

09:43.584 --> 09:46.317
Mary: You're gonna
break his heart.

09:46.353 --> 09:49.020
Mike jr: I thought I wanted
to leave, and then...

09:49.056 --> 09:51.022
I started working
at the station, and...

09:51.157 --> 09:53.692
I like it.
Like, a lot.

09:53.694 --> 09:55.760
Mary: You entitled
little arsehole!

09:55.829 --> 09:57.629
Why should you be
the only one in the family

09:57.764 --> 09:59.030
Who gets to do what he likes?

09:59.165 --> 10:01.032
Mike jr: Mom!
For the first time in my life,

10:01.068 --> 10:04.703
I feel like I'm...
Good at something!

10:04.838 --> 10:06.838
Please?

10:06.907 --> 10:11.175
I've never felt this way
about anything before.

10:11.244 --> 10:14.045
You think you could at least
give me a chance?

10:14.081 --> 10:16.715
You're gonna have to be
the one to tell your father.

10:16.850 --> 10:18.850
Because if you're gonna be
running around his back,

10:18.852 --> 10:24.255
You're gonna have to
do it to his face.

10:24.324 --> 10:26.724
[door shuts]

10:33.466 --> 10:36.600
What ya doing?

10:36.637 --> 10:38.002
Pop: Len marshall died.

10:38.038 --> 10:39.937
Mark: The guy
with his wife's teeth?

10:40.007 --> 10:41.739
Yes, how did you know?

10:41.775 --> 10:43.408
Mark: Well, you told me
this morning.

10:43.477 --> 10:45.143
I'm so sorry for your loss.

10:45.145 --> 10:47.945
Pop: Ah...

10:47.981 --> 10:50.348
He was my last
living childhood friend.

10:50.417 --> 10:51.615
That's it!

10:51.652 --> 10:55.019
I'm an endangered species now.

10:55.088 --> 10:57.088
If you liked him so much,
then why are you

10:57.124 --> 10:58.623
Cutting him out
of all your pictures?

10:58.758 --> 11:00.791
Pop: Because I can't stand
to see dead eyes

11:00.827 --> 11:02.426
Staring at me from the walls.

11:02.462 --> 11:05.229
When somebody dies,
they're dead to me.

11:05.298 --> 11:06.363
Full stop.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.633
Do you want me to go
to the funeral with you?

11:08.768 --> 11:10.802
Pop: No, I'm not going.
Mark: Why not?

11:10.804 --> 11:12.570
Pop: Well, he's not
coming to mine, is he?

11:12.706 --> 11:13.938
Mark: Hm.
Pop: Funny.

11:14.007 --> 11:17.175
Best friends never get to go
to each other's funeral.

11:17.310 --> 11:19.310
Adult mark:<i> Pop acted</i>
<i> like he was letting go,</i>

11:19.379 --> 11:21.312
<i> But his friend's death</i>
<i> had left a hole</i>

11:21.314 --> 11:23.581
<i> Bigger than even he could cut.</i>

11:23.717 --> 11:26.517
Mark: Pop?
Pop: Mm-hm?

11:26.586 --> 11:31.189
Mark: What's the worst part
of losing someone you love...

11:31.191 --> 11:32.256
Like?

11:37.597 --> 11:38.796
There's a difference,
you know,

11:38.865 --> 11:42.233
Between telling a story
and sharing one.

11:42.368 --> 11:45.336
Now, I could tell you about
the time that me and len

11:45.338 --> 11:49.006
Stole apples from a barrel
when we were kids.

11:49.042 --> 11:52.076
But if len was here,

11:52.079 --> 11:54.612
He'd probably argue,
"nah, they're weren't apples,

11:54.614 --> 11:57.649
"they were oranges," you know?

11:57.651 --> 12:00.018
There's just...

12:00.153 --> 12:03.621
No one to reminisce with.

12:03.690 --> 12:06.157
They're not memories.

12:06.292 --> 12:08.760
They're just ghost stories now.

12:10.830 --> 12:12.363
You could make new memories.

12:12.432 --> 12:15.500
Change doesn't
have to be the end.

12:15.569 --> 12:18.203
Not all your friends are gone.

12:18.205 --> 12:22.507
[chuckles]
you're right.

12:22.509 --> 12:23.941
Onwards.

12:23.977 --> 12:25.643
Mark: Onwards.

12:25.712 --> 12:28.780
[both chuckle]

12:28.849 --> 12:31.048
Mark: [sighs]

12:31.084 --> 12:35.386
[sentimental music]

12:35.522 --> 12:38.189
♪

12:38.191 --> 12:41.526
♪

12:41.661 --> 12:46.331
♪

12:46.466 --> 12:50.201
♪

12:50.203 --> 12:52.537
♪

