14:08.949 --> 14:09.914
Millard: What's wrong?

14:10.049 --> 14:11.081
Fox: Nothing.
I'm late.

14:11.117 --> 14:13.618
Millard: Wait, what?
Are you--

14:13.753 --> 14:16.688
Adult mark:<i> The only way</i>
<i> to know you really had love</i>

14:16.823 --> 14:21.292
<i> Is to lose it.</i>

14:21.294 --> 14:23.894
Silver fox: Ow!
What was that for?

14:23.930 --> 14:25.630
Middle fox: [laughs]

14:25.699 --> 14:28.833
Ow!
B'y!

14:28.968 --> 14:32.236
♪

14:42.148 --> 14:43.514
Dick: Always cut on the angle.

14:43.650 --> 14:45.049
That's it.
Perfect!

14:45.118 --> 14:47.285
Radio's in your blood, buddy.

14:47.354 --> 14:50.287
Mike jr: Can we turn it on?
Dick: Yes, b'y.

14:52.792 --> 14:56.961
Dick: That's it now.
Yeah.

14:57.096 --> 14:58.462
There you go.

14:58.464 --> 14:59.964
Give'r.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.598
[jingle music plays on tape]

15:01.635 --> 15:03.467
<i> ♪ you're a part of</i>
<i> the wide world... ♪</i>

15:03.536 --> 15:05.937
Dick [on tape]:
<i> It's the vocm morning show!</i>

15:06.006 --> 15:09.407
<i> Stay in bed a little longer,</i>
<i> me lovelies, with dick dunphy!</i>

15:09.409 --> 15:12.409
Mike sr: [sighs]
good god.

15:12.445 --> 15:14.678
Dick: So,
ya tell yer old man yet?

15:14.714 --> 15:17.815
Mike jr: Nah.
My mom says I should, but...

15:17.951 --> 15:19.883
I don't think I have
the heart for it.

15:19.920 --> 15:21.218
Dick: He'll get over it.

15:21.354 --> 15:23.488
What do you need university
for, anyway, man?

15:23.490 --> 15:25.889
That's for eggheads, brother.

15:25.926 --> 15:27.659
You belong in radio.

15:27.794 --> 15:30.627
Oh...
Thanks, dick.

15:30.664 --> 15:34.165
And hey, maybe I can be
as good as you someday.

15:34.167 --> 15:35.399
[knocking on window]

15:35.468 --> 15:37.234
Mike sr: You greasy prick,
god forgive me!

15:37.270 --> 15:38.903
You got that boy ruined!

15:38.972 --> 15:40.571
What the hell do you know
about univer--

15:40.573 --> 15:43.240
[silence]

15:43.276 --> 15:45.109
Gotta patch him through.
You remember how?

15:45.244 --> 15:46.644
Mike jr: Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Uh...

15:46.779 --> 15:47.812
Studio one.

15:47.814 --> 15:49.247
Mic up.
Fade on.

15:49.382 --> 15:51.115
Mike sr: You bugger!
You ruined his life!

15:51.184 --> 15:53.518
Dick: Jeez, b'y, mike!
I never done nudding!

15:53.520 --> 15:54.785
The boy is good.

15:54.821 --> 15:56.254
Almost as good as me.

15:56.256 --> 15:57.788
Mike sr: And your mother
knows about this?

15:57.790 --> 15:58.723
I'm a newsman!

15:58.725 --> 16:00.725
How the hell am I
the last person on earth

16:00.860 --> 16:02.259
To find out my son's a drop-out?

16:02.295 --> 16:03.861
Dick, you are nothing
but a no good--

16:03.997 --> 16:05.329
[button clicks]
[silence]

16:05.365 --> 16:06.864
Dick: That there's
the mute button.

16:06.933 --> 16:08.666
You wants to know where that is.

16:08.668 --> 16:09.801
Mike jr: Yeah.

16:09.936 --> 16:14.605
[rock sting]

16:14.641 --> 16:16.274
[school bell rings]

16:16.409 --> 16:18.943
It's a nice day.
Take your lunch outside.

16:18.945 --> 16:20.178
Get some fresh air.

16:20.180 --> 16:24.782
I could use a smoke.

16:24.818 --> 16:26.817
You only live once!

16:28.989 --> 16:32.823
[indistinct chatter in hallway]

16:35.929 --> 16:37.594
Fox: Hey...

16:39.899 --> 16:41.331
So, what...

16:41.368 --> 16:43.167
Do you hate me now?

16:44.103 --> 16:45.937
Yes.

16:45.939 --> 16:47.438
No.

16:47.440 --> 16:50.107
I dunno, I...
I just thought that...

16:51.011 --> 16:53.644
What?

16:53.680 --> 16:57.248
Nothing.

16:57.317 --> 16:59.583
Fox: I never even seen
you all summer.

16:59.652 --> 17:03.687
And summer was
like another world.

17:03.723 --> 17:05.056
And then...

17:05.125 --> 17:06.924
I just...

17:06.926 --> 17:09.193
I dunno.

17:09.229 --> 17:11.729
You know?

17:11.864 --> 17:15.166
No.

17:15.301 --> 17:17.201
Adult mark:<i> There was</i>
<i> nothing more to say.</i>

17:17.336 --> 17:19.003
<i> Whatever it was, it was gone.</i>

17:19.005 --> 17:22.273
<i> Like glass, a broken heart</i>
<i> might one day be fixed,</i>

17:22.342 --> 17:25.742
<i> But you will always</i>
<i> see the crack.</i>

17:30.483 --> 17:32.550
Mary: You promised me
you would tell him.

17:32.685 --> 17:36.020
Mike sr: I never should
have let you work up there.

17:36.022 --> 17:37.822
You can still go to university.

17:37.891 --> 17:39.223
You can still be somebody.

17:39.259 --> 17:41.692
Mike jr: I don't need to go to
university to be somebody, dad.

17:41.828 --> 17:43.760
Mike sr: Who are you
gonna be, dick dunphy?

17:43.797 --> 17:44.796
Mary: Jesus, mike!

17:44.931 --> 17:47.030
Even dick dunphy doesn't
want to be dick dunphy.

17:47.067 --> 17:49.300
Mike jr: Did you ever think,
even for a second, dad,

17:49.369 --> 17:52.303
That I want to be like you?

17:52.372 --> 17:55.006
You always say that radio
is nothing to be proud of.

17:55.008 --> 17:56.040
You know what?

17:56.175 --> 17:59.310
I'm proud of you.

17:59.445 --> 18:01.412
Even if you're not.

18:01.414 --> 18:05.783
[sentimental music]

18:05.852 --> 18:09.320
♪

18:14.794 --> 18:17.594
Mark: [sighs]

18:17.630 --> 18:21.999
["at this moment"
by billy vera plays]

18:22.001 --> 18:22.966
[sighs]

18:25.438 --> 18:30.207
<i> ♪ what did you think ♪</i>

18:30.276 --> 18:34.811
<i> ♪ I would do at this moment ♪</i>

18:34.848 --> 18:39.650
<i> ♪ when you're</i>
<i> standing before me...</i> ♪

18:39.686 --> 18:42.687
Well, looks like I'm not
the only one who's lost someone.

18:42.822 --> 18:44.688
Mark: [sighs]

18:44.757 --> 18:49.961
Why can't things just
stay the way they are?

18:50.096 --> 18:52.163
Pop: [sighs]

18:52.298 --> 18:53.630
Have you ever heard the phrase,

18:53.666 --> 18:56.033
"there's plenty more
fish in the sea?"

18:56.035 --> 19:00.238
Yeah, well, now, a fish
may love living in a pond,

19:00.240 --> 19:03.374
But if he just swam
a little bit further,

19:03.376 --> 19:06.543
He'd find that there's
a whole ocean out there.

19:06.579 --> 19:08.446
Unless, of course,
something eats him.

19:08.448 --> 19:11.716
[chuckles]
now, that reminds me...

19:11.718 --> 19:13.684
Do you know what's for supper?

19:14.821 --> 19:16.420
I'm not hungry.

19:16.422 --> 19:17.588
I've got a toothache.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.657
Pop: Really?
Ooh, let me have a look!

19:19.726 --> 19:20.591
Mark: Uh...

19:20.593 --> 19:22.459
Pop: Let me see!
Here, let me see.

19:22.495 --> 19:24.228
Uh-oh!
Oh, yeah.

19:24.297 --> 19:26.463
Your last baby tooth is loose.

19:26.533 --> 19:27.864
Alright, head back.
Mark: Ah!

19:27.901 --> 19:29.800
Go on, back!
Hang on!

19:29.836 --> 19:31.602
Ah!
Got it!

19:31.638 --> 19:34.205
Well... Looks like
somebody's growing up.

19:34.207 --> 19:36.907
[tooth clinks into glass]
pop: Onwards.

19:36.976 --> 19:38.209
Mark: [sighs]

19:38.211 --> 19:39.309
Onwards.

19:39.345 --> 19:41.412
Pop: [chuckles]

